               <p>JAMES PARSONS. I am a <rs id="t18280703-50-viclabel259" type="occupation">butcher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280703-50-victim427 t18280703-50-viclabel259"></join>, and live in Wilstead-street, Somer's-town. The prisoner was occasionally employed to go on errands for me. On the 30th of May I sent him to Mr. Brown, at Kentish-town, with this money; it was the change out of a sovereign - I did not see him again till the Tuesday evening following, when I took him at Battle-bridge - he said, "I know I have done wrong."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280703-50-person428">
                  SARAH 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18280703-50-person428" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
