                  </persName>
            . I expected this money in change for a sovereign which I had sent to pay a bill, but I did not receive it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280703-50-person429">
                  ROBERT 
                  TEASDALE
               <interp inst="t18280703-50-person429" type="surname" value="TEASDALE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280703-50-person429" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280703-50-person429" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I received the prisoner in charge - he said he had taken the money - that he had been overpersuaded by a boy named Robins - they had been into the country, and that morning Robins had run off with the remainder of the money; I have known him from his birth, and never knew him to do anything wrong.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 15.</p>
